reviews_data.review_text: Nice place. But they got our order wrong after we repeated our order twice.

I can’t express enough the way that anyone who knows me knows Press & Porter is like a second home to me. I’ve loved it ever since I moved to Concord in 2020. I love the baristas, they’re welcoming and warm and the community I see every time I come in makes me so happy to live in downtown. The coffee (my favorite is the Maggie) and other options (my favorite specifically The Goldberry iced tea) is amazing. There’s so many seating options inside and outside, so much natural light, a small play area for kiddos, breakfast (get a breakfast sandwich, it’s worth an little wait) and lunch options and plenty of bakery items. I get so much work done here, it’s my happy place. Please shop local and do yourself a favor by going to P&P.

Literally leaving another review because I love this place so much. I'm so happy to see them thriving now that the construction is done in downtown. The owners are just amazing and know me by name because I've come here so often the past few years! No matter who's working as your barista, though, they're all so kind and friendly here. Not only is the coffee fantastic, but they always have fun specials that are truly thoughtfully crafted and delicious. The tiramisu latte is the most recent hit! I'm happy to be back in the area just to have Press & Porter close by again!!! ♡♡♡

reviews_data.review_text:
We bought the Giggle Water. Iced lates tasted like plastic. might be the syrups they use if they recently switched, because it didn't taste like that a few months ago when ordering the same drink. I've had this plastic taste when a barista poured my shot directly into the plastic cup from the espresso machine, instead of pouring my shot onto the icy milk.

Didn't realize it was bad until after the first few sips. Will try again another time and bring it to the staffs attention on my next visit if the plastic taste remains.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi, we do not pour hot shots into plastic cups without milk or ice first. The plastic taste is not a complaint we have ever heard and hate that you had that experience. Anytime you do not like your drink, please do let us know so that we can remake this to your liking. We also have always used the same exact syrup brand for the past 6 years.

We first started frequenting P&P in late 2021, and has become a weekly (often multiple times a week) tradition for us. The coffee and espresso is incredible. The drink menu is vast and well developed and we have ordered “off menu” to great success. There is a “favorites” menu from baristas and locals that has some unique and wonderful drinks on it. The pastries and quick bites are very good. Try an affogato on a hot summer afternoon or a gingerbread latte in the winter, you won’t be disappointed.

The baristas are welcoming, professional, and highly skilled. The owners take incredible care of the shop, keep the menu fresh and exciting, and have always delivered a great experience. We love the feeling of community when we come in to visit.

I used to take advantage of the free (and fast!) Wi-Fi to complete my coursework and study for exams. I never had trouble finding a table and an outlet to myself or to share with someone else doing computer work. The noise level is what you would expect for a community coffee house. It has plenty of comfortable seating to relax and hang out in. Board games are available upon request, and there are plenty of books and toys for the younger ones.

Despite the construction woes, P&P has stayed a beacon of the community and is a powerful voice in the push to shop (and drink great coffee!) small.

reviews_data.review_text:
I come to this coffee shop when I'm in town. Today I came in and waited in line. There was a woman and gentlemen in front of me. While she was giving her order, another man and woman came in and got in line behind me. Apparently, the people in front of me where meeting up with the people behind me. The lady in front of me invited them to get in front of me and, at first, they refused. The lady continued to give her order and again invited the couple behind me to get in front of me, which at this point, they did. The lady that invited them to get in front of me turned and said to me "They're with me: Sorry". The cashier paused and looked at them and me and then took the order of the two people that had gotten in front of me. I normally have a great experience at this coffee shop (and would probably still recommend them) But this experience left a bad taste in my mouth.

The cashier taking the two other people's order before mine caused a long wait for me: which is in the control of the shop. I would have just said something while I was there but I've been struggling with aphasia and talking in public can be embarrassing sometimes. So going to places where I can type out my order and show it makes things easier. But trying to type out why I don't think someone else should be allowed to get in front of me, shouldn't be necessary.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi K.O. Really sorry to hear you had a bad experience, though reading your review- seems you are critical of the customers and not necessarily our shop. We could not have changed the events that happened today to make your experience any better. Its unfortunate that something so minor would cause you to leave such a poor review as we are a small business in the middle of a full blown construction site and reviews like this affect us greatly. I can understand if you had a long wait time, or your drink was wrong or the barista was rude… but everything you described was out of our control.
